  "content": "ner's superpower isn't better CSS &mdash;<br>\n    it's the ability to <strong>look at the screen and react</strong>.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">05 / 08</div>\n</div>\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<!-- SLIDE 6: THE FIX — PLAYWRIGHT MCP               -->\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">The Fix</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\">\n    Give AI <span class=\"highlight-green\">Eyes.</span><br>\n    Playwright MCP.\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\">\n    Playwright MCP lets Claude Code launch a browser,<br>\n    render the page, and screenshot what it built.\n  </div>",
